40:43.963 --> 40:53.842
[♪♪♪]

40:55.975 --> 40:58.412
My name is Sasha Klein.

40:58.456 --> 41:02.024
My parents come
from Ludmir, Poland.

41:02.068 --> 41:04.505
I'm Jew.

41:04.549 --> 41:07.029
You got something
to say to me?

41:07.073 --> 41:08.378
Say it now.

41:08.422 --> 41:10.511
Jewish scum!

41:10.555 --> 41:11.730
[Grunts]

41:11.773 --> 41:14.689
[Indistinct]

41:16.735 --> 41:19.651
[Grunting]

41:24.612 --> 41:26.919
[Screaming]

41:31.401 --> 41:35.493
[Screaming and grunting]

41:38.278 --> 41:48.157
[♪♪♪]

42:01.736 --> 42:04.957
I would rather have killed them
all.

42:05.000 --> 42:05.958
DAVID:
Why?

42:10.876 --> 42:15.881
To show the world that as long
as my Meyer Lansky was around,

42:18.840 --> 42:21.147
they could never do that to us,
again.

42:25.760 --> 42:26.935
Never.

42:31.331 --> 42:35.901
Rabbi Weiss calls the act
shameful and deplorable.

42:35.944 --> 42:37.598
The rabbi says
there is no difference

42:37.642 --> 42:40.601
between these so-called
Jewish gangsters

42:40.645 --> 42:42.603
and the Nazi hoodlums
they attacked.

42:48.957 --> 42:51.220
Kosch refuses to take my money.

42:54.876 --> 42:56.748
People look away from me
and the kids

42:56.791 --> 42:58.576
when we walk down the sidewalk.

43:02.362 --> 43:03.842
Now they all know.

43:22.469 --> 43:24.645
Paul, come.

43:24.689 --> 43:25.733
Come.

43:28.257 --> 43:29.650
Buddy, you too.

43:32.784 --> 43:35.177
Leave your father alone.

43:35.221 --> 43:37.005
He's got some thinking to do.

43:37.049 --> 43:38.137
Buddy.

43:43.925 --> 43:45.405
Listen to your mother.

43:45.448 --> 43:55.328
[♪♪♪]

44:04.511 --> 44:06.208
Mr. Lansky,

44:06.252 --> 44:07.949
I'm Lieutenant Haffenden
of the P3 division

44:07.993 --> 44:10.386
of Naval Intelligence.

44:10.430 --> 44:13.041
As I'm sure you know,
the Germans are sabotaging,

44:13.085 --> 44:16.175
and destroying our ships
all over the North Atlantic.

44:16.218 --> 44:19.308
I've read the papers.
It's terrible.

44:19.352 --> 44:22.224
The enemy is here on our shore.

44:22.268 --> 44:23.312
It's only a matter of time

44:23.356 --> 44:25.271
before there's an attack
on our soil.

44:25.314 --> 44:27.273
We need to ferret out
German spies.

44:27.316 --> 44:30.189
Like you, who's got a problem
with the Sicilians.

44:30.232 --> 44:33.496
Because the Sicilians got
a problem with people like you,

44:33.540 --> 44:34.715
the authorities.

44:34.759 --> 44:36.282
The Mafia controls
the waterfront.

44:36.325 --> 44:39.154
Are you suggesting that
I'm affiliated with the Mafia?

44:39.198 --> 44:41.983
I'm a businessman, Lieutenant.

44:42.027 --> 44:44.159
LT. HAFFENDEN:
Of course.

44:44.203 --> 44:47.032
I'll find your spies,

44:47.075 --> 44:49.121
but you got to do me a favor
first.

45:04.832 --> 45:07.705
Mr. Luciano, State Department
has agreed to arrange

45:07.748 --> 45:09.271
for your release from prison.

45:09.315 --> 45:13.275
Twenty four years left
on my sentence,

45:13.319 --> 45:15.713
14 of whom even eligible
for parole.

45:17.540 --> 45:20.021
Meyer.

45:20.065 --> 45:22.720
I know you would do the same
thing for me.

45:27.812 --> 45:29.465
What can I do to help?

45:31.729 --> 45:34.470
They need you to set up
a meeting with Joe Socks.

45:34.514 --> 45:35.863
Joe Socks,

45:35.907 --> 45:39.606
Joe Lanza, local 16975.

45:39.649 --> 45:42.348
United Seafood Workers Union.

45:42.391 --> 45:45.090
I'll arrange for your boys
to get their union cards

45:45.133 --> 45:46.918
and you can begin
your operation.

45:46.961 --> 45:50.095
I was the connection between
the U.S. and the waterfront.

45:50.138 --> 45:52.706
There were German spies working
amongst us.

45:52.750 --> 45:55.274
I extracted whatever
intelligence I could from them

45:55.317 --> 45:57.145
on behalf of the feds.

45:57.189 --> 45:59.234
The fate of the country
depended on us,

45:59.278 --> 46:01.367
and they're looking
to lock me up?

46:01.410 --> 46:03.108
God bless America.

46:07.025 --> 46:08.940
LANSKY: [Voice-over]
I had my men on a dock
hunting Germans

46:08.983 --> 46:10.550
up and down the shore.

46:14.946 --> 46:17.078
We root them out
and have ourselves

46:17.122 --> 46:18.950
a friendly conversation

46:18.993 --> 46:21.779
in the language them cocksuckers
understood only too well.

46:21.822 --> 46:23.693
[Phone ringing]

46:26.696 --> 46:28.524
You got an address?

46:28.568 --> 46:31.789
224 Main Street.

46:31.832 --> 46:34.574
[Indistinct chatter]

46:39.971 --> 46:40.841
Freeze, don't move.

46:40.885 --> 46:42.408
Don't move, you're under arrest.

46:44.062 --> 46:46.760
LANSKY: [Voice-over]
We busted up the whole
German intelligence network.

46:46.804 --> 46:48.849
Blew the cover
on a group of spies

46:48.893 --> 46:52.505
moving artillery, bombs
and cash.

46:52.548 --> 46:55.769
They were planning an enormous
attack on American soil,

46:55.813 --> 46:57.510
but we stopped it.

46:58.772 --> 47:00.295
So, why would you defend
a country

47:00.339 --> 47:02.558
whose government is devoted
to putting you behind bars?

47:02.602 --> 47:05.518
I'm an American and a Jew.

47:05.561 --> 47:08.826
The Germans wanted to destroy
both of those things.

47:08.869 --> 47:11.524
So I wanted to destroy
the Germans.

47:11.567 --> 47:13.308
- And I did.
- OK. But why?

47:13.352 --> 47:15.615
Why was it never
in the in the press?

47:15.658 --> 47:18.574
They could never own up to
the fact that somebody like me

47:18.618 --> 47:21.882
could be capable of doing
any good in this world?

47:21.926 --> 47:24.929
See, I believe this world
is made of shades of gray.

47:24.972 --> 47:27.148
It's never black or white.

47:27.192 --> 47:29.890
So, you never felt compelled to
just set the record straight

47:29.934 --> 47:32.153
and say, Meyer Lansky, patriot.

47:32.197 --> 47:34.112
I think you found the title
of your book.

47:34.155 --> 47:36.505
I'm asking the question.

47:36.549 --> 47:38.943
I never felt the need back then.

47:38.986 --> 47:40.466
Why?

47:40.509 --> 47:44.296
It was currency between me
and the United States.

47:44.339 --> 47:46.907
I assume that if I did favors
for the government,

47:46.951 --> 47:48.648
they would always honor
my loyalty.

47:48.691 --> 47:50.128
And did they?

47:50.171 --> 47:52.086
We haven't gotten to that part
of the story here David.

47:52.130 --> 47:53.131
OK?

47:53.174 --> 47:56.090
The United States,

47:56.134 --> 47:59.441
are not who you think they are,
David.

47:59.485 --> 48:02.444
You're the wandering Jew
just like Lucky said, right?

48:02.488 --> 48:05.839
That's me, the outsider
invited in from the cold

48:05.883 --> 48:08.537
to warm my feet by the fire.

48:08.581 --> 48:10.148
And then sent them
my way again.

48:10.191 --> 48:11.192
Yeah.

48:14.065 --> 48:16.719
You know how that feels,
don't you?

48:16.763 --> 48:18.243
Of what? What?

48:18.286 --> 48:20.201
To be an outsider.

48:20.245 --> 48:21.594
Your father didn't die, David,

48:21.637 --> 48:23.422
he walked out on you
and your family

48:23.465 --> 48:26.555
and you felt like an outsider
ever since in this world.

48:30.081 --> 48:31.517
Yeah.

48:31.560 --> 48:32.997
[Lansky chuckles]

48:33.040 --> 48:34.694
Look at us here.

48:34.737 --> 48:38.002
Couple of outsiders sitting here
in a diner.

48:44.660 --> 48:46.749
[indistinct chattering]

48:46.793 --> 48:47.620
RAY:
Don't fucking lie.

48:47.663 --> 48:48.403
[indistinct chattering]

48:48.447 --> 48:49.361
RAY:
That's bullshit.

48:49.404 --> 48:50.884
No.

48:50.928 --> 48:52.930
Maureen, I am gonna ask you
one more fucking time,

48:52.973 --> 48:54.061
who fucking snitched?

48:54.105 --> 48:55.497
I don't fucking know.

48:55.541 --> 48:56.498
I swear on my fucking,
I have no idea.

48:56.542 --> 48:57.586
- That's bullshit.
- You okay?

48:57.630 --> 48:58.805
Who the fuck is that?

48:58.848 --> 48:59.632
David, please don't,
we're just talking.

48:59.675 --> 49:00.807
RAY:
Don't fucking lie.

49:00.850 --> 49:01.677
I swear my fucking life,
I have no idea.

49:01.721 --> 49:02.591
- You're shaking.
- I'm not shaky.

49:02.635 --> 49:03.853
Hey, take a hike, pal.

49:03.897 --> 49:06.117
Hey, I've got a John fucking
Wayne here, huh?

49:06.160 --> 49:08.989
Let me ask you a question, John.

49:09.033 --> 49:09.947
Are you fucking her?

49:09.990 --> 49:12.384
Jesus, Ray.

49:12.427 --> 49:13.602
I don't think it is any
of your business, buddy.

49:13.646 --> 49:15.996
I'll tell you
why is my fucking business

49:16.040 --> 49:17.650
because she's got
a big fucking mouth.

49:17.693 --> 49:19.608
- Fuck you.
- And if I can't trust her,

49:19.652 --> 49:21.219
I can't trust any of her
fuck buddies either.

49:21.262 --> 49:22.916
Don't disrespect her, okay?

49:24.744 --> 49:26.267
You put your fucking bag down,
pal.

49:26.311 --> 49:27.921
Ray, please don't do this.

49:27.965 --> 49:29.053
Yeah, put your fucking bag-

49:30.489 --> 49:32.186
God dammit.

49:32.230 --> 49:33.796
You're a fucking asshole Ray.

49:33.840 --> 49:34.928
It's your fucking warning.

49:34.972 --> 49:36.147
Keep your mouth shut.

49:40.629 --> 49:43.415
MAUREEN:
He was busted for selling drugs.

49:43.458 --> 49:44.633
Someone set him up.

49:49.073 --> 49:51.118
I told a girlfriend of mine
I was in Miami.

49:51.162 --> 49:52.511
She told him where I was.

49:54.730 --> 49:57.690
So he showed up wanting to know
if I know who set him up.

49:59.866 --> 50:00.998
Do you?

50:03.304 --> 50:04.349
No.

50:09.832 --> 50:12.618
We all make mistakes.

50:12.661 --> 50:13.836
Ray was one of mine.

50:20.539 --> 50:22.932
Life is just full of shades
of grey.

50:22.976 --> 50:32.855
[♪♪♪]

50:46.043 --> 50:47.392
She likes it rough, huh?

50:50.177 --> 50:52.005
Who did that to you?

50:52.049 --> 50:53.267
DAVID:
It's nothing.

50:53.311 --> 50:54.051
Either you're going to tell me
who did this

50:54.094 --> 50:55.356
or I'm going to find out.

50:58.446 --> 51:02.407
All right, well, okay you know,
the woman that I've been...

51:02.450 --> 51:06.019
Fucking?
I think that's the word for it.

51:06.063 --> 51:09.979
Yeah, OK, well, I had to break
up a fight between her

51:10.023 --> 51:12.547
- and her ex.
- [Lansky laughs]

51:12.591 --> 51:14.680
I see.

51:14.723 --> 51:18.292
Well, I wish you luck with all
your future sparring endeavors.

51:18.336 --> 51:19.815
Thank you, nice.

51:19.859 --> 51:22.731
LANSKY:
My pleasure.
Next time hit him first.

51:22.775 --> 51:24.646
Always hit him first.

51:26.561 --> 51:30.522
Mr. Lansky,
you chose the losing side.

51:30.565 --> 51:36.919
I'm a businessman,
I don't choose sides.

51:36.963 --> 51:38.878
We chose opportunities.

51:38.921 --> 51:41.968
Which is why I think we can make
a deal.

51:42.011 --> 51:44.057
DAVID: [Voice-over]
Salvatore Maranzano,

51:44.101 --> 51:47.191
possible bosses
of organized crime in New York.

51:47.234 --> 51:49.802
Bootlegging, racketeering,
narcotics.

51:49.845 --> 51:51.543
He called himself Little Caesar.

51:54.328 --> 51:56.939
I want to invest
in your corporate joints.

51:56.983 --> 52:03.685
See, the thing is, I built my
business from the ground up

52:03.729 --> 52:07.211
and I prefer to keep it under
the same roof.

52:07.254 --> 52:10.431
[Salvatore chuckles]

52:10.475 --> 52:14.218
And frankly, Mr. Maranzano,
I don't need your money.

52:17.960 --> 52:23.401
Yeah, I don't give a shit,
how's that look?

52:23.444 --> 52:25.054
What if I offer you
an opportunity

52:25.098 --> 52:28.275
to take Luciano's seat
in the council?

52:28.319 --> 52:30.277
How you propose doing that?

52:30.321 --> 52:33.585
You take Luciano out
and the seat's yours.

52:33.628 --> 52:35.064
He'll never see it coming
from you.

52:39.330 --> 52:41.158
You walk out now

52:41.201 --> 52:42.768
or we'll take you down
with the restaurant.

52:47.990 --> 52:53.474
I have known Luciano
for a long time,

52:53.518 --> 52:56.782
since we were children.

52:56.825 --> 52:59.176
He's much more than an associate
to me.

52:59.219 --> 53:01.830
I respect that.

53:01.874 --> 53:05.443
But there can only be one boss,
and that's me.

53:05.486 --> 53:07.793
It's about business.

53:07.836 --> 53:09.708
I think you should make
the right decision here

53:09.751 --> 53:11.318
and do the right thing.

53:11.362 --> 53:12.493
We've got a search warrant.

53:13.625 --> 53:15.192
Hey, nobody move.

53:15.235 --> 53:16.367
Nobody move!
Hey!

53:16.410 --> 53:17.542
What's all the commotion?

53:17.585 --> 53:18.804
Go check it out, Marco.

53:21.850 --> 53:26.072
Woah, woah, woah, calm down.
Put down your guns.

53:26.115 --> 53:28.335
My boss is inside,
you go talk to him.

53:28.379 --> 53:29.684
He knows your Captain.
It's going to be OK.

53:29.728 --> 53:31.382
Everything's all right.
Hey.

53:34.602 --> 53:36.213
- [Gunshot]
- [Grunting]

53:36.256 --> 53:38.650
What took you so long?

53:38.693 --> 53:39.694
Lot of stairs.

53:39.738 --> 53:41.043
[Gunshots in distance]

53:41.087 --> 53:43.698
Double crossing prick.

53:43.742 --> 53:45.004
Make him feel it, Benny.

53:45.047 --> 53:46.397
No.

53:46.440 --> 53:47.267
- Come here.
- No.

53:47.311 --> 53:50.227
[Groaning]

53:51.489 --> 53:53.186
Look at me, look at me
when you fucking die,

53:53.230 --> 53:55.057
you double crossing
sack of shit.

53:58.496 --> 53:59.888
Oh, that's it.

54:02.674 --> 54:03.849
Here you go.

54:12.074 --> 54:15.295
They're going to come after us
now,

54:15.339 --> 54:17.297
all of them with everything
they've got.

54:17.341 --> 54:20.605
We'll already be in control
by then.

54:20.648 --> 54:22.607
I'm grateful for your loyalty,
Meyer.

54:25.653 --> 54:28.177
I want a seat at the council,
Charlie.

54:28.221 --> 54:29.657
It's a new era,

54:29.701 --> 54:31.616
what matters is
how I run my business,

54:31.659 --> 54:33.313
not the fact that I'm a Jew.

54:33.357 --> 54:35.054
You know, if it were up to me--

54:35.097 --> 54:36.795
We'll be your executors,

54:36.838 --> 54:39.058
seen the numbers
we're doing in Saratoga.

54:39.101 --> 54:41.626
No one runs an operation
like I do.

54:41.669 --> 54:46.370
I got the best carpet joints,
Upstate, Jersey, Florida.

54:46.413 --> 54:48.546
No, you don't gotta justify it
to me, Meyer.

54:48.589 --> 54:50.852
Plus, I got the muscle to back
all of 'em.

54:50.896 --> 54:55.204
And the revenue,
the revenue speaks for itself.

54:55.248 --> 55:01.472
I run it like a business
and Ford Motors, Coca-Cola.

55:01.515 --> 55:03.604
You know, like U.S. Steel.

55:07.695 --> 55:11.264
I'll tell you what,

55:11.308 --> 55:13.005
I'll do what I can
to convince the council

55:13.048 --> 55:14.398
that you deserve a spot.

55:14.441 --> 55:15.399
Hmm.

55:17.749 --> 55:18.663
What about Benny?

55:18.706 --> 55:21.013
Benny.

55:21.056 --> 55:23.189
Benny's handling California
for us?

55:30.631 --> 55:32.198
Why are you still awake?

55:32.241 --> 55:34.635
How the hell
am I supposed to sleep?

55:34.679 --> 55:36.158
Do you know what time it is?

55:36.202 --> 55:38.335
Yeah, says the man who comes
and goes at all hours.

55:38.378 --> 55:40.641
Mind your business.

55:40.685 --> 55:41.903
Was out working.

55:41.947 --> 55:43.644
Oh work.

55:43.688 --> 55:45.429
It's always work with you.

55:45.472 --> 55:47.648
Take a look around you.

55:47.692 --> 55:50.216
All this shit.

55:50.259 --> 55:52.827
Where do you think
it comes from, huh?

55:52.871 --> 55:55.743
Maybe try showing
a little gratitude for once.

55:55.787 --> 55:58.267
Gratitude?

55:58.311 --> 56:02.402
The hell with gratitude,
you're a criminal.

56:02.446 --> 56:03.185
Come on.

56:03.229 --> 56:04.622
[Grunting]

56:04.665 --> 56:07.755
[Taking deep breaths]

56:12.456 --> 56:15.110
What happened to you?

56:15.154 --> 56:16.590
You're pathetic.

56:20.464 --> 56:24.424
You think the neighbors
don't talk to you because of me?

56:24.468 --> 56:27.340
I see in your eyes
what you do at night.

56:27.384 --> 56:30.648
Who do you think you are
coming into our home

56:30.691 --> 56:32.780
pretending to be a good man,
huh?

56:32.824 --> 56:34.956
A father?

56:35.000 --> 56:37.524
You think you're helping him?

56:37.568 --> 56:38.395
[Grunts]

56:38.438 --> 56:40.962
Shut your mouth!

56:41.006 --> 56:43.095
It's your fault.

56:43.138 --> 56:45.706
It's your fault he's a cripple.

56:45.750 --> 56:48.013
It's because of you,
it's all because of you!

56:51.103 --> 56:52.583
[Sobs]

56:52.626 --> 56:56.021
It's called "judgement",
it's punishment

56:56.064 --> 56:57.109
for what you've done

56:57.152 --> 56:59.633
and how you live your life,
Meyer.

57:01.853 --> 57:04.769
[Sobs]

57:07.119 --> 57:08.468
God is watching.

57:08.512 --> 57:12.733
He's watching,
he's watching you, I know he is.

57:12.777 --> 57:15.693
[Sobbing]

57:24.571 --> 57:26.921
DAVID:
You believe that?

57:26.965 --> 57:28.488
Believe what?

57:28.532 --> 57:33.275
We get judged and punished
for the way we live our lives.

57:33.319 --> 57:37.497
The choices we make
that's what defines us.

57:37.541 --> 57:39.847
I don't question the choices
I make.

57:39.891 --> 57:41.283
Never?

57:41.327 --> 57:43.285
I get the feeling sometimes
you don't question

57:43.329 --> 57:45.592
the choices you make either.

57:45.636 --> 57:47.551
Okay, let's talk
about those choices.

57:49.596 --> 57:51.511
Tell me about Murder, Inc.

57:51.555 --> 57:53.774
After Maranzano,

57:53.818 --> 57:57.474
we needed the muscle
to consolidate our power.

57:57.517 --> 57:59.476
I had the right people to do it.

58:01.478 --> 58:02.479
Bingo.

58:04.916 --> 58:07.745
LANSKY: [Voice-over]
A group of nice Jewish
and Italian boys,

58:07.788 --> 58:10.617
you know, the kind a girl wants
to bring home to her mother.

58:10.661 --> 58:12.750
Always willing to lend a hand.

58:12.793 --> 58:15.840
[Grunting & yelling]

58:15.883 --> 58:19.670
DAVID: [Voice-over]
"Murder, Inc.",
that's what they called them.

58:19.713 --> 58:23.543
There was Abe "Kid Twist" Reles,
"Tick-Tock" Tannenbaum,

58:23.587 --> 58:27.504
Louis "Lepke" Buchalter,
an army of enforcers,

58:27.547 --> 58:30.681
hired assassins,
a thousand hits between 'em,

58:30.724 --> 58:33.684
they put contract killers
on payroll.

58:33.727 --> 58:35.555
There were no rules
on how to kill.

58:35.599 --> 58:39.907
As long as you got it done,
you got paid.

58:39.951 --> 58:43.650
Most were shot, stabbed,
strangled, drowned, burned,

58:43.694 --> 58:48.307
buried alive, left to bleed dry,
all of 'em unrepentant,

58:48.350 --> 58:50.744
cold-blooded killers.

58:50.788 --> 58:53.573
And Lansky was their general.

58:53.617 --> 58:56.445
Through sheer determination
and fearlessness,

58:56.489 --> 58:59.013
Lansky finally got
what he wanted,

58:59.057 --> 59:01.625
a seat at the table
sitting right beside guys like

59:01.668 --> 59:06.368
Joe Bonnano, Frank Costello,
Al Capone, Italian--

59:06.412 --> 59:08.414
- Meyer.
- To Meyer.

59:08.457 --> 59:10.590
DAVID: [Voice-over]
Jewish and Irish mob bosses
from across America,

59:10.634 --> 59:12.810
together, they formed
the largest organization

59:12.853 --> 59:15.029
of crime the world
has ever known,

59:15.073 --> 59:16.814
the National Crime Syndicate.

59:30.479 --> 59:32.090
I don't know understand

59:32.133 --> 59:33.308
when they're investigating
Lansky,

59:33.352 --> 59:35.702
no one bothered to look
at the old files.

59:35.746 --> 59:38.705
Hey, we're talking 40 years
of transcripts, depositions,

59:38.749 --> 59:40.707
surveillance reports.

59:40.751 --> 59:42.579
That's a lot of material.

59:42.622 --> 59:45.843
Frank, look at this.

59:45.886 --> 59:47.235
It says he's still alive.

59:50.543 --> 59:54.721
Mr. Sims, I'm Special Agent
Frank Rivers with the FBI.

59:56.941 --> 59:58.682
[Grunts]

59:58.725 --> 1:00:01.075
I'd like to talk to you
about your association

1:00:01.119 --> 1:00:02.381
with Meyer Lansky.

1:00:02.424 --> 1:00:05.036
Never heard of him.

1:00:05.079 --> 1:00:07.647
I can make your life in here
a whole lot easier, you know.

1:00:07.691 --> 1:00:09.736
I'm gonna die in here.

1:00:09.780 --> 1:00:11.520
The hell are you gonna do
for me?

1:00:11.564 --> 1:00:13.087
Get me fresh soup?

1:00:13.131 --> 1:00:16.438
Well, Lansky sent you on a job
and you got caught

1:00:16.482 --> 1:00:19.050
and right now he's uh--

1:00:19.093 --> 1:00:20.965
he's having
a pretty comfortable life,

1:00:21.008 --> 1:00:22.488
and you're stuck in here.

1:00:22.531 --> 1:00:24.403
You gonna pop him for me,
are you?

1:00:24.446 --> 1:00:25.752
I can put him away.

1:00:25.796 --> 1:00:27.580
Make it so his life's
not a whole lot different

1:00:27.624 --> 1:00:29.495
from yours.

1:00:29.538 --> 1:00:31.802
I'm looking for his money.

1:00:31.845 --> 1:00:34.892
He started stashing it away
back in the Murder, Inc. days.

1:00:34.935 --> 1:00:37.068
So who was keeping the books
back then?

1:00:37.111 --> 1:00:39.244
- No money.
- What do you mean no money?

1:00:39.287 --> 1:00:41.289
There's no money in murder.

1:00:41.333 --> 1:00:47.034
It wasn't a sustainable business
not like a casino.

1:00:47.078 --> 1:00:48.209
There was money.

1:00:48.253 --> 1:00:49.863
Maybe he just didn't tell you
about it,

1:00:49.907 --> 1:00:51.952
he was stuffing the walls
with it.

1:00:51.996 --> 1:00:52.953
[Spits]

1:00:56.174 --> 1:00:58.132
Then go ask the walls.

1:00:58.176 --> 1:01:01.309
You listen to me,
you piece of shit.

1:01:01.353 --> 1:01:05.183
The only reason you're in here
is because of that asshole.

1:01:05.226 --> 1:01:07.925
Well, now you can suffer
the rest of your time in here

1:01:07.968 --> 1:01:09.535
because of him, too.

1:01:11.102 --> 1:01:13.452
Geneva.

1:01:13.495 --> 1:01:15.715
Geneva?

1:01:15.759 --> 1:01:19.153
He had a money manager
in Geneva.

1:01:41.567 --> 1:01:42.829
What are you doing with that?

1:01:47.573 --> 1:01:49.357
What are you doing with it?

1:01:50.532 --> 1:01:51.969
[Shushes]

1:01:52.970 --> 1:01:54.623
FBI.

1:01:58.192 --> 1:02:00.194
DAVID:
Just tell-- just tell me,
tell me.

1:02:00.238 --> 1:02:01.413
Tell me, it's okay.

1:02:01.456 --> 1:02:03.197
What-- what is it?

1:02:03.241 --> 1:02:05.156
Ray turned state's
evidence,

1:02:05.199 --> 1:02:07.898
he made a deal with the Feds,
they reduced his sentence.

1:02:07.941 --> 1:02:09.203
And he named me
as one of his partners

1:02:09.247 --> 1:02:10.509
in his drug operation.

1:02:10.552 --> 1:02:12.337
So the Feds came to me
and they said that

1:02:12.380 --> 1:02:14.382
I would go to prison
if I didn't cooperate.

1:02:14.426 --> 1:02:15.688
Okay.

1:02:18.125 --> 1:02:19.431
So how?

1:02:19.474 --> 1:02:20.562
It's "cooperate"
that's the word that they used?

1:02:20.606 --> 1:02:22.173
Get close to you.

1:02:24.436 --> 1:02:28.179
Okay, and then?

1:02:28.222 --> 1:02:30.747
Feed them information
from your files.

1:02:33.662 --> 1:02:37.797
Listen, David, everything
that's been happening between us

1:02:37.841 --> 1:02:39.756
is real.

1:02:39.799 --> 1:02:41.932
- You have to trust me.
- Trust you, trust you?

1:02:41.975 --> 1:02:43.063
I know that sounds ridiculous.

1:02:43.107 --> 1:02:44.891
I have a family.

1:02:47.938 --> 1:02:49.983
[Scoffs]

1:02:52.116 --> 1:02:53.813
[Takes deep breaths]

1:02:53.857 --> 1:02:57.382
What did-- did you...

1:02:57.425 --> 1:02:58.252
What'd you give 'em?

1:02:58.296 --> 1:03:00.385
Everything I could remember.

1:03:00.428 --> 1:03:05.869
The name of associates
and accomplices.

1:03:05.912 --> 1:03:07.479
They wanted me to write
everything down

1:03:07.522 --> 1:03:09.089
and give it to them
and that's what I did.

1:03:09.133 --> 1:03:11.526
Okay, what else did they want?

1:03:11.570 --> 1:03:13.746
What else they wanted
apart from names?

1:03:13.790 --> 1:03:15.443
They said you might have
information on money

1:03:15.487 --> 1:03:16.923
that Lansky laundered years ago.

1:03:16.967 --> 1:03:19.012
Money.

1:03:19.056 --> 1:03:20.057
[Scoffs]

1:03:20.100 --> 1:03:29.066
[♪♪♪]

1:03:29.109 --> 1:03:31.808
Oh.

1:03:40.904 --> 1:03:42.862
[Sobs]

1:03:42.906 --> 1:03:52.829
[♪♪♪]

1:04:17.679 --> 1:04:20.508
[Muffled screaming]

1:04:32.129 --> 1:04:33.913
DAVID: [On tape]
What are you doing with that?

1:04:33.957 --> 1:04:35.567
What are you doing with it?

1:04:35.610 --> 1:04:38.265
[Maureen shushes]

1:04:38.309 --> 1:04:41.399
MAUREEN: [On tape]
FBI.

1:04:41.442 --> 1:04:42.704
I'll tell you everything.

1:04:42.748 --> 1:04:52.627
[♪♪♪]

1:04:57.197 --> 1:04:58.982
[Sniffles]

1:05:03.029 --> 1:05:05.858
[Indistinct chatter
in background]

1:05:17.391 --> 1:05:19.132
Okay, here we are again.

1:05:39.109 --> 1:05:41.154
- [Knocking on door]
- Morning.

1:05:41.198 --> 1:05:43.243
Can I help you?

1:05:43.287 --> 1:05:45.680
Special Agent Frank Rivers,
with the FBI.

1:05:45.724 --> 1:05:48.205
We're looking for a guest
of the hotel, Miss Duffy.

1:05:48.248 --> 1:05:50.468
She's in room 1-4-6.

1:05:50.511 --> 1:05:52.165
Miss Duffy's not here.

1:05:52.209 --> 1:05:54.037
Well, I'd like to look
in her room if I could.

1:05:54.080 --> 1:05:55.342
Suit yourself.

1:05:55.386 --> 1:05:57.301
But you're not going to find
anything there.

1:05:57.344 --> 1:05:59.999
- Room's empty.
- Empty?

1:06:00.043 --> 1:06:01.958
Miss Duffy checked out
late last night.

1:06:05.526 --> 1:06:07.789
How did you evade the Feds,

1:06:07.833 --> 1:06:09.748
like how did you
and your business associates

1:06:09.791 --> 1:06:12.620
become so successful under
the scrutiny of the government?

1:06:12.664 --> 1:06:15.275
- Why are you whispering?
- Hmm.

1:06:15.319 --> 1:06:18.322
I can hardly hear you.

1:06:18.365 --> 1:06:23.196
How did you and your associates
like that were very successful

1:06:23.240 --> 1:06:24.589
under the scrutiny
of the government?

1:06:24.632 --> 1:06:26.025
How did you do that?

1:06:26.069 --> 1:06:28.506
The way any legitimate
company does.

1:06:28.549 --> 1:06:32.466
We were making more money
than some Fortune 500 companies.

1:06:32.510 --> 1:06:35.556
We got assets to manage
and we had the best talent

1:06:35.600 --> 1:06:36.993
to manage them.

1:06:37.036 --> 1:06:38.603
You okay, David?

1:06:38.646 --> 1:06:41.519
You seem a little white
around the gills this morning.

1:06:41.562 --> 1:06:42.737
It was one of those nights.

1:06:42.781 --> 1:06:43.608
Not another one.

1:06:43.651 --> 1:06:46.437
[Both laugh]

1:06:46.480 --> 1:06:49.527
Okay, so um, how'd you go about
doing all of that,

1:06:49.570 --> 1:06:51.572
changing your
business practices?

1:06:51.616 --> 1:06:53.574
'Cause I think that's what
everyone wants to know.

1:06:53.618 --> 1:06:56.708
I taught my associates that
there are benefits,

1:06:56.751 --> 1:07:01.278
cost benefit of keeping a guy
that owes you money alive

1:07:01.321 --> 1:07:05.064
instead of goons, I said,
we ought to send accountants.

1:07:05.108 --> 1:07:09.025
Additional sum for
the cash reserve and profit

1:07:09.068 --> 1:07:13.072
should be passed along
to be put in the credit column

1:07:13.116 --> 1:07:14.421
of the ledger.

1:07:14.465 --> 1:07:15.944
There's a reason
I dropped out of school

1:07:15.988 --> 1:07:17.598
when I was 12.

1:07:17.642 --> 1:07:18.512
Let him talk.

1:07:18.556 --> 1:07:19.774
That guy made more money

1:07:19.818 --> 1:07:21.341
for Luciano
than all your tweeds combined.

1:07:21.385 --> 1:07:22.429
- Come on.
- Uh.

1:07:22.473 --> 1:07:23.648
Any questions?

1:07:23.691 --> 1:07:26.259
In the early days,
a man owed you money,

1:07:26.303 --> 1:07:29.741
you would send goons
to break his body apart,

1:07:29.784 --> 1:07:32.787
and if he couldn't pay,
he'd find an unfortunate end.

1:07:32.831 --> 1:07:35.747
Now, rather than kill the guy,
we ordered him,

1:07:35.790 --> 1:07:37.575
crunch the numbers,

1:07:37.618 --> 1:07:39.881
make sure his business
turns a profit.

1:07:39.925 --> 1:07:43.146
Now, Joe Schmo belongs to us.

1:07:43.189 --> 1:07:44.538
We own him.

1:07:44.582 --> 1:07:53.547
[♪♪♪]

1:07:53.591 --> 1:07:55.419
Why don't we go for a walk,
David?

1:07:55.462 --> 1:07:57.638
You look like
you could use some air.

1:07:57.682 --> 1:07:59.162
Come.

1:08:03.209 --> 1:08:07.344
Optimizing our resources,
restructuring our operations.

1:08:07.387 --> 1:08:10.129
This was a new world
for our associates.

1:08:10.173 --> 1:08:12.566
I think it was Henry Ford
that said that,

1:08:12.610 --> 1:08:15.526
"Business that makes nothing
but money is a poor business."

1:08:15.569 --> 1:08:18.311
Gambling and casinos
are to entertainment,

1:08:18.355 --> 1:08:21.749
what Ford's automobile
was to transportation.

1:08:21.793 --> 1:08:22.924
For some business,

1:08:22.968 --> 1:08:24.404
it's to realize
as the toss of the dice.

1:08:24.448 --> 1:08:25.927
We catered to that need.

1:08:25.971 --> 1:08:28.191
Okay, you wake up
in the morning,

1:08:28.234 --> 1:08:31.150
there's car in your driveway,
you didn't make a product.

1:08:31.194 --> 1:08:33.283
[Laughs]

1:08:33.326 --> 1:08:36.416
Henry Ford's product
wasn't the car.

1:08:36.460 --> 1:08:39.593
It was the freedom
the car gave to people.

1:08:39.637 --> 1:08:42.030
Freedom is what people wanted.

1:08:42.074 --> 1:08:44.816
Our product wasn't gambling
or the casinos.

1:08:44.859 --> 1:08:47.297
It was the world of excitement
and thrills.

1:08:47.340 --> 1:08:49.255
We built have resorts
in this country,

1:08:49.299 --> 1:08:53.172
created thousands of jobs,
supported families.

1:08:53.216 --> 1:08:55.087
It was a product.

1:08:55.131 --> 1:08:56.654
That's why
it's all legalized now,

1:08:56.697 --> 1:08:59.787
why the government
has its finger in the pie.

1:08:59.831 --> 1:09:02.834
It was too valuable a product
to leave to criminals.

1:09:12.800 --> 1:09:13.932
David, where's your car?

1:09:13.975 --> 1:09:15.499
It's over there.

1:09:19.242 --> 1:09:21.287
This fucker is following us.

1:09:21.331 --> 1:09:24.856
Can you fucking believe it?

1:09:24.899 --> 1:09:27.380
See if you could turn off
some place,

1:09:27.424 --> 1:09:29.252
make the first turn off you can.

1:09:33.343 --> 1:09:33.952
DAVID:
Here?

1:09:33.995 --> 1:09:35.562
Right over here.

1:09:37.608 --> 1:09:39.175
Son of a bitch.

1:09:39.218 --> 1:09:49.141
[♪♪♪]

1:09:57.976 --> 1:09:58.977
[Sighing]

1:09:59.020 --> 1:10:01.806
Right, so who is that?

1:10:01.849 --> 1:10:03.808
I thought maybe
you could tell me.

1:10:06.202 --> 1:10:08.204
I-- I don't know.

1:10:17.300 --> 1:10:20.868
When you lose your money,
you lose nothing.

1:10:20.912 --> 1:10:24.176
When you lose your health,
you lose something.

1:10:24.220 --> 1:10:27.179
When you lose your character,
you lose everything.

1:10:29.399 --> 1:10:31.270
Remember that.

1:10:31.314 --> 1:10:41.237
[♪♪♪]

1:11:11.658 --> 1:11:14.052
Hey, woman in the room,
you seen her?

1:11:14.095 --> 1:11:16.924
- She checked out.
- She checked out?

1:11:16.968 --> 1:11:18.056
What's going on here?

1:11:18.099 --> 1:11:19.187
I don't want any trouble.

1:11:21.189 --> 1:11:22.843
I'm not giving you any trouble.

1:11:22.887 --> 1:11:26.934
The Do Not Disturb sign has been
on your door for a week.

1:11:26.978 --> 1:11:28.675
Okay, well, let's keep it
that way, alright?

1:11:28.719 --> 1:11:31.635
I'll pay you extra,
you let no one in my room.

1:11:31.678 --> 1:11:32.810
Fine.

1:11:53.221 --> 1:11:56.355
Let's talk about the shitstorm
of trouble you're in, Mr. Stone.

1:11:56.399 --> 1:11:57.791
Show him the pictures, Greg.

1:11:59.489 --> 1:12:00.968
This must have been fun, huh?

1:12:01.012 --> 1:12:04.058
Get a little taste of that.

1:12:04.102 --> 1:12:05.451
You have fun taking these?

1:12:05.495 --> 1:12:06.496
Did you have fun taking them?

1:12:06.539 --> 1:12:07.627
Meyer Lansky has
over $300 million.

1:12:07.671 --> 1:12:08.193
Why are you--
why are showing me this?

1:12:08.236 --> 1:12:09.716
Listen to me.

1:12:09.760 --> 1:12:12.110
Lansky has over $300 million
squirreled away somewhere.

1:12:12.153 --> 1:12:13.198
The government wants it

1:12:13.241 --> 1:12:15.026
and we want your help
finding it.

1:12:15.069 --> 1:12:17.681
I can't, I can't-- I...

1:12:17.724 --> 1:12:20.205
Now we could let it slip
to Mr. Lansky that

1:12:20.248 --> 1:12:24.035
you've been sharing his secrets
with an FBI informant.

1:12:24.078 --> 1:12:26.342
That's not gonna go well
for you.

1:12:26.385 --> 1:12:30.128
Look, we don't wanna go down
that road if we don't have to.

1:12:30.171 --> 1:12:32.391
We know you're just a writer
who was looking for a story

1:12:32.435 --> 1:12:34.045
who had the misfortune
to stumble into

1:12:34.088 --> 1:12:38.005
a decades-long investigation
into Lansky and Associates.

1:12:38.049 --> 1:12:42.009
So we're willing to offer you
a financial incentive,

1:12:42.053 --> 1:12:44.142
we'll make you a paid informant.

1:12:44.185 --> 1:12:46.623
We'll give you $150,000.

1:12:46.666 --> 1:12:48.842
Now that'll go a long way
to take care of your family

1:12:48.886 --> 1:12:49.582
- and your money problems.
- I don't have any--

1:12:49.626 --> 1:12:50.496
I don't need your money.

1:12:50.540 --> 1:12:52.585
David, we've been listening.

1:12:52.629 --> 1:12:55.501
You help us
or Lansky gets to you first.

1:12:55.545 --> 1:12:57.851
Now we can offer you
and your family protection

1:12:57.895 --> 1:12:59.418
and the money.

1:12:59.462 --> 1:13:02.160
The way I see it,
you don't have a choice.

1:13:02.203 --> 1:13:04.118
I'm gonna give you
my number here.

1:13:04.162 --> 1:13:06.643
You call us from a payphone
when you got something.

1:13:08.949 --> 1:13:10.473
Do the right thing here, David.

1:13:30.493 --> 1:13:33.321
You heard the joke about
this rabbi who got hit by a car,

1:13:33.365 --> 1:13:35.889
falls down,
the emergency ambulance comes,

1:13:35.933 --> 1:13:39.023
rabbi's laying on the floor,
the emergency worker runs over,

1:13:39.066 --> 1:13:41.852
says, "Rabbi, Rabbi,
are you okay?"

1:13:41.895 --> 1:13:45.029
The rabbi looks up at him
and he says, "I make a living."

1:13:46.683 --> 1:13:48.336
[Laughing]

1:13:48.380 --> 1:13:49.555
Okay, go ahead.

1:13:49.599 --> 1:13:51.557
A little levity here,
you know.

1:13:51.601 --> 1:13:56.040
Money, must have been pouring in
by now, right?

1:13:56.083 --> 1:13:57.345
That's right.

1:14:01.654 --> 1:14:05.615
CUBAN EMISSARY:
The gaming business in Cuba
is no good,

1:14:05.658 --> 1:14:09.009
it's a free-for-all,
no regulations.

1:14:09.053 --> 1:14:11.795
[Speaks Spanish]

1:14:11.838 --> 1:14:13.536
These men are making millions.

1:14:15.581 --> 1:14:19.280
Gambling in Cuba will soon be
under our control again.

1:14:19.324 --> 1:14:22.240
And President Batista
wants you to oversee it,

1:14:22.283 --> 1:14:23.546
Mr. Lansky.

1:14:23.589 --> 1:14:26.592
All of it.

1:14:26.636 --> 1:14:29.552
I appreciate the opportunity.

1:14:29.595 --> 1:14:33.338
I always felt Cuba,
a land of enterprise.

1:14:35.209 --> 1:14:37.995
In America,
you might be an outlaw,

1:14:38.038 --> 1:14:41.520
but in Cuba
you are on the inside.

1:14:41.564 --> 1:14:44.480
[Lyrics in Spanish]

1:14:44.523 --> 1:14:50.311
[♪♪♪]

1:14:50.355 --> 1:14:52.270
You were making what,
10 million?

1:14:52.313 --> 1:14:56.013
Turned to 20,
and then 30 million.

1:14:56.056 --> 1:14:57.710
I was the biggest
casino operator

1:14:57.754 --> 1:14:59.756
this country had ever seen.

1:14:59.799 --> 1:15:02.323
You were legitimate, yeah,
you were above board.

1:15:02.367 --> 1:15:04.935
You had your license,
machines weren't rigged.

1:15:04.978 --> 1:15:06.502
Never.

1:15:06.545 --> 1:15:08.591
But they still consider you
part of the underworld.

1:15:08.634 --> 1:15:10.854
[Lyrics in Spanish]

1:15:10.897 --> 1:15:13.813
We weren't the underworld.

1:15:13.857 --> 1:15:16.555
We were the overworld.

1:15:21.168 --> 1:15:23.997
[Lyrics in Spanish]

1:15:25.608 --> 1:15:28.088
Go back to sleep.

1:15:33.441 --> 1:15:36.836
DAVID: [Voice-over]
When Batista gave Lansky
control over Cuba's casinos,

1:15:36.880 --> 1:15:39.360
Lansky turned the country
into an international playground

1:15:39.404 --> 1:15:41.798
for gamblers
and pleasure-seekers.

1:15:41.841 --> 1:15:44.278
Criminal empire
outside the U.S.,

1:15:44.322 --> 1:15:46.716
it couldn't be touched
by law enforcement.

1:15:46.759 --> 1:15:48.674
The National Crime Syndicate
now owned

1:15:48.718 --> 1:15:51.416
the biggest gambling corporation
in the world.

1:15:51.459 --> 1:15:52.852
And Lansky was the CEO.

1:15:56.769 --> 1:15:58.379
Hey kid.

1:16:00.468 --> 1:16:03.602
How you doin', huh?

1:16:03.646 --> 1:16:05.430
How was the trip?

1:16:05.473 --> 1:16:06.692
Fine.

1:16:09.652 --> 1:16:11.001
How you doin', beautiful?

1:16:11.044 --> 1:16:12.132
Huh?

1:16:12.176 --> 1:16:13.351
Come on, let's go.

1:16:13.394 --> 1:16:14.570
You wanna go to the room?

1:16:14.613 --> 1:16:15.353
Let's head in.

1:16:15.396 --> 1:16:16.789
Come on.

1:16:16.833 --> 1:16:18.661
[♪♪♪]

1:16:26.886 --> 1:16:29.715
[Indistinct chatter]

1:16:43.294 --> 1:16:45.601
[Cheering]

1:16:51.694 --> 1:16:53.521
YOUNG LANSKY:
You put the nickel in.

1:16:53.565 --> 1:16:54.697
Just try.

1:16:54.740 --> 1:16:57.787
Right here?

1:16:57.830 --> 1:17:00.485
Pull that lever hard.

1:17:00.528 --> 1:17:06.578
State-of-the-art slot and blend,
silent bells, double jackpots

1:17:06.622 --> 1:17:09.668
and then the guys rig 'em
so they better our odds.

1:17:09.712 --> 1:17:11.409
Haven't I talked to you
about that?

1:17:11.452 --> 1:17:12.628
About what?

1:17:14.804 --> 1:17:16.675
I don't want
the machines rigged.

1:17:16.719 --> 1:17:19.809
Every casino in this town
rigs their machines.

1:17:19.852 --> 1:17:23.116
I'm not every casino.

1:17:23.160 --> 1:17:24.378
Yes, sir.

1:17:27.730 --> 1:17:29.296
Come on, go again.

1:17:37.304 --> 1:17:39.306
I'll be right back, Buddy.

1:17:39.350 --> 1:17:40.743
Keep at it.

1:17:40.786 --> 1:17:42.745
You, watch the kid.

1:17:42.788 --> 1:17:52.668
[♪♪♪]

1:17:57.977 --> 1:17:59.849
Mr. Yariv.

1:17:59.892 --> 1:18:02.242
Mr. Lansky,
thank you for seeing me.

1:18:02.286 --> 1:18:04.157
Welcome to the Colonial,
Mr. Yariv.

1:18:05.593 --> 1:18:07.334
Please.

1:18:07.378 --> 1:18:09.380
Thank you.

1:18:09.423 --> 1:18:11.904
How can I help you?

1:18:11.948 --> 1:18:15.429
Mr. Lansky, I'm here on behalf
of Golda Meir.

1:18:15.473 --> 1:18:17.954
As you know, our people
have been slaughtered in Germany

1:18:17.997 --> 1:18:19.259
and across Europe.

1:18:19.303 --> 1:18:20.565
The Jewish settlement
in Palestine

1:18:20.608 --> 1:18:21.871
has been hard at work.

1:18:21.914 --> 1:18:22.915
You need money?

1:18:22.959 --> 1:18:24.308
Yes.

1:18:24.351 --> 1:18:26.527
To purchase weapons.

1:18:26.571 --> 1:18:28.529
We are fighting for
the future state of Israel

1:18:28.573 --> 1:18:31.141
and for the survival of
the Jewish people, Mr. Lansky.

1:18:31.184 --> 1:18:34.840
Fighting, as in killing.

1:18:42.979 --> 1:18:46.069
We will do whatever it takes,
Mr. Lansky.

1:18:48.854 --> 1:18:52.423
You tell Miss Meir that

1:18:52.466 --> 1:18:55.774
she has Meyer Lansky's support.

1:18:55.818 --> 1:18:58.777
I'd be happy to contribute
in any way.

1:18:58.821 --> 1:19:01.824
And I'm sure my colleagues here
share my feelings

1:19:01.867 --> 1:19:03.390
for the state of Israel.

1:19:04.957 --> 1:19:07.917
Well, how much do you have
on you.

1:19:07.960 --> 1:19:10.789
It's the weekend take.

1:19:10.833 --> 1:19:12.008
Give it to him.

1:19:22.888 --> 1:19:25.761
Mr. Yariv here
is taking donations

1:19:25.804 --> 1:19:27.240
for the state of Israel.

1:19:27.284 --> 1:19:28.764
I am Italian.

1:19:52.222 --> 1:19:54.572
I'll make arrangements for more.

1:19:54.615 --> 1:19:57.053
On behalf of Golda Meir
and the Israeli people,

1:19:57.096 --> 1:19:58.968
we are grateful.

1:19:59.011 --> 1:20:00.752
And we will not soon forget.

1:20:11.894 --> 1:20:14.287
If you need any weapons
or ammunition,

1:20:14.331 --> 1:20:15.985
you let me know.

1:20:16.028 --> 1:20:17.769
We hope you enjoy your stay
with us.

1:20:17.813 --> 1:20:19.989
Oh, I'm not staying
at the Colonial.

1:20:21.642 --> 1:20:23.644
Next time, I hope.

1:20:38.616 --> 1:20:41.184
We're hearing things, Meyer,
about Ben.

1:20:42.925 --> 1:20:45.231
What kind of things?

1:20:45.275 --> 1:20:47.668
That he's out of control,
kicking heads in,

1:20:47.712 --> 1:20:50.019
dating movie stars.

1:20:50.062 --> 1:20:52.630
He's lost his focus, Meyer.

1:20:52.673 --> 1:20:55.154
We gave him California,
we gave him Vegas,

1:20:55.198 --> 1:20:57.940
all's we get in return is grief.

1:20:57.983 --> 1:20:59.898
I'll talk to him.

1:20:59.942 --> 1:21:01.769
Envelopes are coming back
lighter.

1:21:02.945 --> 1:21:06.252
Listen,
Lucky ain't happy, Meyer.

1:21:08.385 --> 1:21:12.955
You know, it ain't easy for us
coming to you like this

1:21:12.998 --> 1:21:15.000
not gonna shout Ben.

1:21:15.044 --> 1:21:19.178
I said I'll talk to him.

1:21:31.799 --> 1:21:35.412
So what are you gonna do
with your winnings, huh?

1:21:37.327 --> 1:21:40.243
Buy mom a new fur coat,
just like you always do.

1:21:40.286 --> 1:21:43.637
Your mother-- your mother,
she's got plenty of fur coats.

1:21:43.681 --> 1:21:46.814
I'm gonna be just like you.

1:21:46.858 --> 1:21:49.295
I'm gonna get my wife
fur coats, too.

1:21:54.866 --> 1:21:57.129
Or you can be whatever
you wanna be.

1:21:59.958 --> 1:22:01.917
You don't wanna be like me.

1:22:09.837 --> 1:22:11.361
Why?

1:22:15.191 --> 1:22:17.149
You just don't.

1:22:18.455 --> 1:22:22.372
[Takes deep breath]

1:22:27.072 --> 1:22:32.077
I love you, you know that,
right?

1:22:32.121 --> 1:22:34.384
I love you, too.

1:22:47.963 --> 1:22:51.923
I never wanted my children
to follow in my footsteps.

1:22:51.967 --> 1:22:53.838
You know, I think about it
all the time.

1:22:57.929 --> 1:23:01.933
My kids see me as a--
a man who tries his best

1:23:01.977 --> 1:23:04.501
or-- or some failure?

1:23:04.544 --> 1:23:07.025
It's complicated.

1:23:07.069 --> 1:23:09.897
Marriage, children,
you did your best.

1:23:09.941 --> 1:23:12.117
[Scoffs]

1:23:12.161 --> 1:23:14.076
I trust you, David.

1:23:14.119 --> 1:23:16.078
You're gonna write
a hell of a book.

1:23:22.693 --> 1:23:24.086
Vegas.

1:23:24.129 --> 1:23:26.479
Vegas, Flamingo.

1:23:28.351 --> 1:23:32.268
LANSKY: [Voice-over]
We built that town,
a paradise,

1:23:32.311 --> 1:23:35.227
but for us it turned out to be
our worst nightmare.

1:23:35.271 --> 1:23:38.013
[Phone ringing]

1:23:53.506 --> 1:23:54.507
[Grunts]

1:23:54.551 --> 1:23:55.813
- Yeah.
- Benny.

1:23:55.856 --> 1:23:57.510
YOUNG BEN: [On phone]
Meyer, that you?

1:23:59.991 --> 1:24:01.166
What time is it?

1:24:01.210 --> 1:24:03.734
It's a quarter after 2:00 there.

1:24:03.777 --> 1:24:04.996
Look, why don't you
hop on a flight

1:24:05.040 --> 1:24:06.650
and head out here?

1:24:06.693 --> 1:24:09.131
Oh, hey pal, listen,
I'd love to,

1:24:09.174 --> 1:24:10.828
but you know, Ginny's
got friends in town, right?

1:24:10.871 --> 1:24:13.396
So probably not for me.

1:24:15.224 --> 1:24:18.792
Hey, I gotta tell you,
the women in this town, man.

1:24:18.836 --> 1:24:20.229
[Laughs]

1:24:20.272 --> 1:24:21.969
Meyer, you'd go crazy.

1:24:22.013 --> 1:24:24.059
I'm happy things are good
for you, Ben,

1:24:24.102 --> 1:24:26.322
but unfortunately, we have to
talk about something

1:24:26.365 --> 1:24:28.106
not so pleasant.

1:24:28.150 --> 1:24:29.238
Well, what is it?

1:24:29.281 --> 1:24:30.978
It's our investors.

1:24:32.458 --> 1:24:33.894
- They're not happy.
- What do you mean?

1:24:33.938 --> 1:24:35.418
Is there--
did they tell you that?

1:24:35.461 --> 1:24:37.028
YOUNG LANSKY: [On phone]
Can you blame them?

1:24:37.072 --> 1:24:41.424
The materials are overpriced,
the construction is delayed.

1:24:41.467 --> 1:24:43.861
YOUNG BEN: [On phone]
Do you know how many people
are undertaking this town?

1:24:43.904 --> 1:24:46.037
I can't screw in a light bulb
without a city official

1:24:46.081 --> 1:24:47.952
and he's goddamn maid
coming for a handout.

1:24:47.995 --> 1:24:50.041
- That's the deal.
- The accounting is sloppy, Ben

1:24:50.085 --> 1:24:51.912
and sloppy accounting
leads to concern.

1:24:51.956 --> 1:24:53.131
Do me a favor.

1:24:53.175 --> 1:24:55.394
Remind them that
we own 66% of this casino,

1:24:55.438 --> 1:24:57.788
which means we get to decide
who gets to be concerned.

1:24:57.831 --> 1:25:00.617
66% of nothing is nothing.

1:25:00.660 --> 1:25:03.620
We have to put money back in
to cover the cash flow problem.

1:25:07.189 --> 1:25:09.582
Were you planning on talking
to me about this?

1:25:09.626 --> 1:25:11.497
Of course.

1:25:11.541 --> 1:25:13.020
Of course, I mean
what'd you think

1:25:13.064 --> 1:25:16.328
I wasn't gonna have that
conversation with you?

1:25:16.372 --> 1:25:19.505
How much are we talking about,
Ben?

1:25:19.549 --> 1:25:20.680
Half a million.

1:25:22.508 --> 1:25:25.076
Maybe another three
just to get us

1:25:25.120 --> 1:25:26.425
through a few months.

1:25:30.037 --> 1:25:31.517
I'll turn it around, Meyer.

1:25:32.997 --> 1:25:35.826
I know you will, Ben.

1:25:35.869 --> 1:25:37.697
That's what I told Lucky.

1:25:40.744 --> 1:25:43.921
I'm not gonna let you down,
I swear.

1:25:43.964 --> 1:25:45.140
I know, Ben.

1:25:54.105 --> 1:25:56.412
You're listening to my calls?

1:25:56.455 --> 1:25:57.630
He's a bum.

1:26:00.242 --> 1:26:03.245
He's a bum and you know it.

1:26:03.288 --> 1:26:05.203
YOUNG LANSKY:
It's not your concern, Anne.

1:26:05.247 --> 1:26:07.205
He's gonna get you killed.

1:26:07.249 --> 1:26:09.599
They'll kill you both.

1:26:09.642 --> 1:26:10.817
Bang, bang.

1:26:12.471 --> 1:26:14.995
Goodbye, Meyer Lansky.

1:26:15.039 --> 1:26:16.562
May he rest in peace.

1:26:18.216 --> 1:26:21.306
Father.

1:26:21.350 --> 1:26:23.265
Husband.

1:26:23.308 --> 1:26:24.701
Murderer.

1:26:24.744 --> 1:26:28.008
- Stay out of this.
- How about I jump, huh?

1:26:28.052 --> 1:26:28.966
Right off this balcony
and save you all that trouble.

1:26:29.009 --> 1:26:31.708
Don't be ridiculous.

1:26:31.751 --> 1:26:32.970
Come on.

1:26:33.013 --> 1:26:35.451
Would make your day.

1:26:35.494 --> 1:26:38.845
Don't pretend like you care
for my well-being.

1:26:40.456 --> 1:26:44.503
All you care for is your money.

1:26:44.547 --> 1:26:47.506
It's your money,
money, money, money, money.

1:26:47.550 --> 1:26:48.377
- Your money.
- Enough!

1:26:48.420 --> 1:26:50.901
- [Grunting]
- No!

1:26:50.944 --> 1:26:53.556
You murderer, you're a murderer!

1:26:53.599 --> 1:26:55.210
Get off!
Liar!

1:26:55.253 --> 1:26:58.169
[Grunting]

1:27:00.911 --> 1:27:02.260
Get off me!

1:27:02.304 --> 1:27:04.088
No!

1:27:04.131 --> 1:27:06.090
- [Grunting]
- Hey, call an ambulance.

1:27:06.133 --> 1:27:07.483
- No, Meyer!
- It's my wife.

1:27:07.526 --> 1:27:09.180
- No, Meyer.
- She's hysterical.

1:27:09.224 --> 1:27:10.355
No!

1:27:10.399 --> 1:27:13.532
- Meyer!
- [Indistinct speech]

1:27:13.576 --> 1:27:15.752
Just get a doctor here now!

1:27:23.716 --> 1:27:25.544
[♪♪♪]

1:27:34.684 --> 1:27:35.641
[Zapping]

1:27:35.685 --> 1:27:38.688
[Grunting]

1:27:38.731 --> 1:27:48.611
[♪♪♪]

1:28:02.102 --> 1:28:03.713
Well, God damn.

1:28:06.281 --> 1:28:08.631
Meyer, oy.

1:28:09.806 --> 1:28:10.502
Look at this place.

1:28:11.590 --> 1:28:12.461
Nice, hmm.

1:28:12.504 --> 1:28:14.289
[Laughs]

1:28:14.332 --> 1:28:15.638
Are you kidding me?

1:28:15.681 --> 1:28:17.509
You're the king
of the goddamn domain.

1:28:17.553 --> 1:28:20.120
I'll tell you something, too.

1:28:20.164 --> 1:28:22.688
It'll be little different
down here.

1:28:22.732 --> 1:28:23.428
How's your flight?

1:28:23.472 --> 1:28:27.040
Ah, forget about that.

1:28:27.084 --> 1:28:29.739
Real question is, what do
we got lined up for tonight?

1:28:29.782 --> 1:28:31.958
Hmm.

1:28:32.002 --> 1:28:33.830
Oh, boy.

1:28:33.873 --> 1:28:35.527
[Laughs]

1:28:38.225 --> 1:28:39.618
Things have changed, Ben.

1:28:39.662 --> 1:28:42.882
Look around you.

1:28:42.926 --> 1:28:47.147
There's too much money at stake
to be fucking around.

1:28:47.191 --> 1:28:48.453
We're not kids anymore.

1:28:48.497 --> 1:28:49.628
Yeah.

1:28:51.804 --> 1:28:53.284
You're right.

1:28:53.328 --> 1:28:54.981
I can't keep defending you.

1:28:57.244 --> 1:28:59.290
Especially if you don't show
any results.

1:28:59.334 --> 1:29:00.639
Is that what you doin'?

1:29:01.988 --> 1:29:03.207
You're defending me?

1:29:03.250 --> 1:29:04.251
Meyer I used to know,

1:29:04.295 --> 1:29:05.644
he would've stood up
for his pal.

1:29:13.652 --> 1:29:18.265
You know, there was never
an option for me.

1:29:19.963 --> 1:29:22.966
Wasn't gonna be a tailor's son,
make 8 bucks a week?

1:29:25.925 --> 1:29:27.231
But you could have
done anything.

1:29:29.973 --> 1:29:32.192
And I looked up to you
my whole life for that.

1:29:39.069 --> 1:29:41.027
And following you.

1:29:43.421 --> 1:29:46.337
[Sighs]

1:29:46.381 --> 1:29:48.470
I don't know, Meyer.

1:29:48.513 --> 1:29:50.254
I don't know
if it was worth my soul.

1:29:54.127 --> 1:29:56.129
'Cause I don't know
how to get that back.

1:30:15.714 --> 1:30:22.329
I'm aware that I was called here
today to bear witness

1:30:22.373 --> 1:30:29.728
to your decision
to kill my friend, Ben Siegel.

1:30:29.772 --> 1:30:32.427
And he saved my life
on more than one occasion.

1:30:35.212 --> 1:30:40.957
I cannot sit here and watch you
condemn him to death.

1:30:41.000 --> 1:30:43.873
But he's been robbin' from us,
Meyer.

1:30:43.916 --> 1:30:47.703
I'm aware of
Benny's shortcomings.

1:30:47.746 --> 1:30:55.188
I'm also aware that many of us
would not be sitting here today

1:30:55.232 --> 1:30:58.191
if it weren't for Benny's
past loyalty

1:30:58.235 --> 1:31:02.108
and his willingness
to stick out his neck.

1:31:05.938 --> 1:31:08.288
If it's about money,

1:31:08.332 --> 1:31:10.900
I've agreed to make amends
for his past mistakes.

1:31:12.989 --> 1:31:18.995
If it's about honor,
I ask you

1:31:19.038 --> 1:31:22.955
where is the honor in killing
a friend?

1:31:22.999 --> 1:31:32.791
[♪♪♪]

1:31:32.835 --> 1:31:35.054
Why don't you step outside,
Meyer?

1:31:35.098 --> 1:31:44.977
[♪♪♪]

1:31:56.989 --> 1:32:00.427
INVESTOR #1:
In the matter of Bugsy Siegel...

1:32:00.471 --> 1:32:02.125
Ay.

1:32:02.168 --> 1:32:03.605
Ay.

1:32:03.648 --> 1:32:04.562
Ay.

1:32:04.606 --> 1:32:06.085
Ay.

1:32:06.129 --> 1:32:07.434
Ay.

1:32:07.478 --> 1:32:08.392
Ay.

1:32:12.483 --> 1:32:13.615
Ay.

1:32:13.658 --> 1:32:23.538
[♪♪♪]

1:32:30.545 --> 1:32:32.895
[Gunshots]

1:32:41.730 --> 1:32:44.602
[Phone ringing]

1:32:57.789 --> 1:32:59.399
Hello.

1:32:59.443 --> 1:33:01.358
EVA: [On phone]
Daddy.

1:33:01.401 --> 1:33:02.272
Eva?

1:33:02.315 --> 1:33:04.840
EVA: [On phone]
Yes.

1:33:04.883 --> 1:33:07.320
Eva, what are you--
what are you doing up?

1:33:07.364 --> 1:33:08.931
What time is it?

1:33:08.974 --> 1:33:11.847
EVA: [On phone]
I couldn't sleep.

1:33:11.890 --> 1:33:13.152
"I couldn't sleep."

1:33:13.196 --> 1:33:14.937
Honey, you gotta get to sleep.

1:33:14.980 --> 1:33:16.547
Got school tomorrow.

1:33:16.591 --> 1:33:20.203
EVA: [On phone]
But tomorrow is Saturday.

1:33:20.246 --> 1:33:22.640
Okay.

1:33:22.684 --> 1:33:24.511
Where's your mama?

1:33:24.555 --> 1:33:27.602
EVA: [On phone]
She went out.

1:33:27.645 --> 1:33:29.647
She went out, out where?

1:33:29.691 --> 1:33:31.388
EVA: [On phone]
With some man.

1:33:35.653 --> 1:33:37.046
You know, these things.

1:33:38.700 --> 1:33:41.616
It's-- that's what's
gonna happen, you know.

1:33:45.445 --> 1:33:49.275
EVA: [On phone]
Daddy,
do you still love mommy?

1:33:52.017 --> 1:33:54.150
Honey, I love you.

1:33:56.935 --> 1:33:58.937
I love you.

1:34:00.504 --> 1:34:03.246
FRANK:
Mrs. Lansky.

1:34:03.289 --> 1:34:04.813
Who is it?

1:34:04.856 --> 1:34:08.294
FRANK:
It's Frank Rivers, ma'am,
we spoke on the phone.

1:34:08.338 --> 1:34:10.253
Oh, yes.

1:34:10.296 --> 1:34:12.124
I remember.

1:34:12.168 --> 1:34:13.691
Sit down.

1:34:13.735 --> 1:34:15.171
Thank you.

1:34:20.263 --> 1:34:22.657
You know, there's no way in hell
you're going to find

1:34:22.700 --> 1:34:25.050
that bastard's money.

1:34:25.094 --> 1:34:26.312
Why is that?

1:34:27.836 --> 1:34:31.187
My ex-husband, Meyer,

1:34:31.230 --> 1:34:34.581
he never let a dime
out of his sight.

1:34:34.625 --> 1:34:36.018
[Chuckles]

1:34:39.238 --> 1:34:43.025
If I were you,
I would look to Cuba.

1:34:43.068 --> 1:34:46.985
That is where Meyer made
his first real money.

1:34:47.029 --> 1:34:49.727
I thought he lost everything
when Castro took over.

1:34:49.771 --> 1:34:52.512
You think he would
give all that money

1:34:52.556 --> 1:34:54.123
to a communist.

1:34:55.559 --> 1:34:59.432
Uh, that Batista,
he trusted no one, only Meyer.

1:35:01.826 --> 1:35:03.915
He gave Meyer
what Meyer wanted.

1:35:05.830 --> 1:35:07.963
FRANK:
And what was that?

1:35:08.006 --> 1:35:11.488
To turn that country
into the Monte Carlo

1:35:11.531 --> 1:35:12.968
of the Caribbean.

1:35:16.711 --> 1:35:20.323
If only it had lasted.

1:35:20.366 --> 1:35:21.846
Pfft.

1:35:21.890 --> 1:35:24.806
[Waves crashing]

1:35:26.938 --> 1:35:29.114
Here's one of his diets.

1:35:29.158 --> 1:35:31.595
Matiz Sardine, Jello,
and Irish stew.

1:35:31.638 --> 1:35:33.553
- Blegh.
- Ugh.

1:35:33.597 --> 1:35:37.557
Hey, there's a Lansky associate
in Geneva.

1:35:37.601 --> 1:35:39.298
GREG:
That might be our guy.

1:35:39.342 --> 1:35:42.040
Let's get Stone to run it
by Lansky.

1:35:42.084 --> 1:35:44.869
I got it, of course.

1:35:44.913 --> 1:35:48.568
Hey David,
I got a message for you.

1:35:48.612 --> 1:35:50.266
From Mr. Lansky.

1:36:11.461 --> 1:36:13.028
What-- what do you want?

1:36:13.071 --> 1:36:15.247
I'm beginning to think
you're not taking me seriously.

1:36:15.291 --> 1:36:16.292
Hey, he's not even here.

1:36:16.335 --> 1:36:17.772
I've got nothing.

1:36:17.815 --> 1:36:18.729
Man, I think we're done.

1:36:18.773 --> 1:36:19.817
I think the book is done.

1:36:19.861 --> 1:36:21.079
- I think--
- Listen to me.

1:36:21.123 --> 1:36:22.602
We're looking for an associate
of Lansky's.

1:36:22.646 --> 1:36:25.257
He goes by the name "Pinkus".

1:36:25.301 --> 1:36:26.824
He's 81, alright?

1:36:26.868 --> 1:36:28.826
He's mind's not that sharp.

1:36:28.870 --> 1:36:30.915
I think that some of the stuff
he's been saying is--

1:36:30.959 --> 1:36:32.308
it's a little incoherent.

1:36:32.351 --> 1:36:34.832
Trust me,
he'll remember this name.

1:36:34.876 --> 1:36:38.140
Find out who he is, okay?

1:36:38.183 --> 1:36:39.619
You've got a pen,
I'll write it down.

1:36:39.663 --> 1:36:42.753
Pink-ass,
that you could remember.

1:36:47.714 --> 1:36:49.499
[Knocking on door]

1:36:51.762 --> 1:36:52.937
LANSKY: [On radio]
Hello, David.

1:36:52.981 --> 1:36:54.547
Come in, come in.

1:36:56.462 --> 1:36:58.856
I didn't feel like
going out today.

1:36:58.900 --> 1:37:00.162
You want coffee?

1:37:00.205 --> 1:37:01.250
DAVID:
No, thanks, I'm fine.

1:37:05.950 --> 1:37:07.386
Is that your father?

1:37:15.394 --> 1:37:17.483
When Israel turned me down,

1:37:17.527 --> 1:37:19.616
all I could think about was
how embarrassed

1:37:19.659 --> 1:37:20.922
he would have been.

1:37:22.924 --> 1:37:25.665
I was always ashamed of him.

1:37:25.709 --> 1:37:28.233
In my mind, he was weak.

1:37:28.277 --> 1:37:30.496
Busting his balls
earning pennies.

1:37:32.107 --> 1:37:35.762
He felt the same about me,
shame

1:37:35.806 --> 1:37:38.113
for having a gangster
for a son.

1:37:44.902 --> 1:37:48.036
I didn't go to his funeral,
my own father.

1:37:50.690 --> 1:37:52.997
I don't have the power
to change my past,

1:37:53.041 --> 1:37:56.131
I do have the power to change
the perception of it.

1:37:57.784 --> 1:38:00.875
Do as I ask
and you will be rewarded.

1:38:03.181 --> 1:38:05.314
You would do what I ask.

1:38:05.357 --> 1:38:06.576
Let's sit on the porch.

1:38:06.619 --> 1:38:07.272
GREG:
Turn it back now.

1:38:07.316 --> 1:38:08.099
Switch over to two.

1:38:14.758 --> 1:38:15.933
What's going on?

1:38:15.977 --> 1:38:18.631
We lost, he knows
we're listening to him.

1:38:18.675 --> 1:38:19.850
Goddammit.

1:38:24.333 --> 1:38:26.596
There's a name that came up
in my research,

1:38:26.639 --> 1:38:27.945
someone named "Pinkus".

1:38:31.906 --> 1:38:33.342
Huh?

1:38:33.385 --> 1:38:35.213
Someone named "Pinkus".

1:38:38.434 --> 1:38:42.655
You mean Sal Rosenstein,
tough son of a bitch,

1:38:42.699 --> 1:38:45.963
his entire family died
at Takhel.

1:38:46.007 --> 1:38:48.574
After the war,
he moved to Switzerland,

1:38:48.618 --> 1:38:51.099
did some banking for me.

1:38:51.142 --> 1:38:53.536
Pinkus was my nickname for him.

1:38:58.628 --> 1:39:02.762
Wanted Pinkus' identity,
get a pen.

1:39:02.806 --> 1:39:04.939
Saul Rosenstein.

1:39:06.766 --> 1:39:08.203
Yeah, yeah.

1:39:08.246 --> 1:39:09.465
Put the money
in my wife's account

1:39:09.508 --> 1:39:10.901
and make sure they're safe.

1:39:10.945 --> 1:39:12.511
And let my family alone.

1:39:18.778 --> 1:39:20.389
[Sighs]

1:39:23.958 --> 1:39:25.960
We found him.

1:39:26.003 --> 1:39:27.831
Who, Rosenstein?

1:39:27.874 --> 1:39:29.876
Yeah, he was in Geneva.

1:39:29.920 --> 1:39:30.790
Where is he now?

1:39:30.834 --> 1:39:32.227
He died 48 hours ago.

1:39:32.270 --> 1:39:35.143
[Phone ringing]

1:39:49.809 --> 1:39:52.029
Yeah, what the--

1:39:52.073 --> 1:39:54.249
FRANK: [On phone]
It's Rivers, Saul Rosenstein
was killed in a car accident

1:39:54.292 --> 1:39:56.860
- 48 hours ago.
-Say again.

1:39:56.903 --> 1:39:58.557
FRANK: [On phone]
I'm saying that Lansky
had him killed.

1:39:58.601 --> 1:40:00.211
This is not a coincidence.

1:40:00.255 --> 1:40:02.300
I would advise you
to stop talking to Lansky.

1:40:02.344 --> 1:40:12.267
[♪♪♪]

1:40:15.835 --> 1:40:17.576
Mr. Rivers,
as soon as you called,

1:40:17.620 --> 1:40:20.101
we started running a query
into our database.

1:40:20.144 --> 1:40:22.233
It appears Mr. Rosenstein
moved his money

1:40:22.277 --> 1:40:24.801
primarily to one place, Israel.

1:40:24.844 --> 1:40:27.064
Rosenstein was Mossad.

1:40:27.108 --> 1:40:29.153
We've got a paper trail
of laundered money

1:40:29.197 --> 1:40:32.678
going in and out of Geneva
into Israel to a bank

1:40:32.722 --> 1:40:34.202
called "Mekif".

1:40:34.245 --> 1:40:36.030
And you think that money
was Lansky's?

1:40:36.073 --> 1:40:38.075
I think it's why Lansky wanted
to get into Israel.

1:40:38.119 --> 1:40:39.337
His money's there.

1:40:45.213 --> 1:40:48.172
MEKIF EMPLOYEE:
Mr. Rivers,
welcome to Israel.

1:40:48.216 --> 1:40:50.087
We've been expecting you.

1:40:50.131 --> 1:40:52.176
I will be taking you down
to the vault.

1:40:57.051 --> 1:40:59.183
Here it is.

1:40:59.227 --> 1:41:00.706
Thank you.

1:41:00.750 --> 1:41:10.673
[♪♪♪]

1:41:18.202 --> 1:41:19.551
Son of a bitch.

1:41:19.595 --> 1:41:21.162
And God said to Abraham,

1:41:21.205 --> 1:41:26.123
"Abraham, take your son,
your only son whom you love,

1:41:26.167 --> 1:41:29.735
Isaac, and sacrifice him
upon one of the mountains

1:41:29.779 --> 1:41:31.520
that I will tell you."

1:41:31.563 --> 1:41:36.002
And Abraham went forth
with Isaac to do just that.

1:41:36.046 --> 1:41:39.223
But perhaps what God
really wanted was for Abraham

1:41:39.267 --> 1:41:42.357
to say, no.

1:41:42.400 --> 1:41:46.143
We praise God now for those
who have departed this world

1:41:46.187 --> 1:41:49.842
as we stand for the Kaddish,
let us all stand.

1:41:51.888 --> 1:41:54.717
[Jewish prayer in Aramaic]

1:42:08.861 --> 1:42:10.776
Mr. Lansky, Mr. Lansky.

1:42:10.820 --> 1:42:13.039
David.

1:42:13.083 --> 1:42:14.258
Prayer for the dead, right?

1:42:14.302 --> 1:42:15.172
Kaddish.

1:42:15.216 --> 1:42:16.521
Is that for your father?

1:42:16.565 --> 1:42:18.871
Or was it for Saul Rosenstein?

1:42:18.915 --> 1:42:23.789
Remember Saul Rosenstein,
your friend Pinkus is dead

1:42:23.833 --> 1:42:25.051
and he died in a car accident.

1:42:26.357 --> 1:42:27.750
I'm sorry to hear that.

1:42:27.793 --> 1:42:29.012
Three days ago.

1:42:32.450 --> 1:42:34.757
Are you suggesting
I had something to do with it?

1:42:34.800 --> 1:42:36.280
I just think
it's a bit coincidental,

1:42:36.324 --> 1:42:37.586
we were just talking about him

1:42:37.629 --> 1:42:41.242
and then something terrible
happens to him.

1:42:41.285 --> 1:42:43.026
[Laughs]

1:42:43.069 --> 1:42:45.071
Maybe he's dead

1:42:45.115 --> 1:42:47.683
or maybe they just think
he's dead.

1:42:47.726 --> 1:42:49.250
Just tell me the truth.

1:42:49.293 --> 1:42:51.687
You mean like the truth that
you're speaking to the Feds?

1:42:54.777 --> 1:42:57.214
You betrayed me, David,
you broke my heart,

1:42:57.258 --> 1:42:59.651
you made a deal with me
and you broke your word.

1:42:59.695 --> 1:43:01.131
Yeah, I did talk to them.

1:43:01.175 --> 1:43:03.481
I did, yeah.

1:43:03.525 --> 1:43:06.267
You know why I did it?

1:43:06.310 --> 1:43:08.094
You call it "self-preservation",
I think.

1:43:08.138 --> 1:43:11.010
Right, I had to do
what I had to do for my family.

1:43:11.054 --> 1:43:12.186
Stand by.

1:43:14.275 --> 1:43:15.885
I forgive you, David.

1:43:17.495 --> 1:43:20.019
If you wanna hear
the rest of the story...

1:43:20.063 --> 1:43:22.152
Why'd you forgive me?

1:43:22.196 --> 1:43:23.675
'Cause I like you.

1:43:25.111 --> 1:43:28.158
You liked Sal Rosenstein, too.

1:43:28.202 --> 1:43:29.246
Not really.

1:43:34.077 --> 1:43:37.472
INTERVIEWER:
And now you come to Israel,
for what reason?

1:43:37.515 --> 1:43:39.735
You want to become
an Israeli citizen, Mr. Lansky?

1:43:39.778 --> 1:43:42.216
I do.

1:43:42.259 --> 1:43:47.133
My association with Israel
stands many years back.

1:43:47.177 --> 1:43:49.266
I was born a Jew.

1:43:49.310 --> 1:43:52.095
I have all my life
lived as a Jew.

1:43:52.138 --> 1:43:55.229
I never changed my faith.

1:43:55.272 --> 1:43:57.535
My grandparents are buried here.

1:43:57.579 --> 1:44:00.669
INTERVIEWER:
Why are the American authorities
after you?

1:44:00.712 --> 1:44:04.020
LANSKY:
They claim I have 50%
of Lebanon casinos,

1:44:04.063 --> 1:44:05.978
50% of Monte Carlo.

1:44:06.022 --> 1:44:10.287
INTERVIEWER:
Mr. Lansky, is there such
a thing as organized crime?

1:44:10.331 --> 1:44:12.985
I have no knowledge
on the subject

1:44:13.029 --> 1:44:15.553
and I'd like to live
the remainder of my days

1:44:15.597 --> 1:44:16.989
in Israel.

1:44:24.040 --> 1:44:29.872
I got a tip from a friend,
Golda Meir's lobbying Nixon

1:44:29.915 --> 1:44:32.918
to supply Israel
with F-4 fighter bombers.

1:44:32.962 --> 1:44:34.485
What's that got to do with me?

1:44:34.529 --> 1:44:37.096
The prime minister was told that
in order for that deal

1:44:37.140 --> 1:44:38.315
to go through,

1:44:38.359 --> 1:44:40.578
she'd have to see to that
you leave Israel

1:44:40.622 --> 1:44:42.363
and return to the U.S.

1:44:42.406 --> 1:44:45.670
State Department
is revoking your passport.

1:44:45.714 --> 1:44:47.890
You need to surrender
at the embassy.

1:44:47.933 --> 1:44:52.286
The Law of Return says
every Jew has the right

1:44:52.329 --> 1:44:56.159
to citizenship in Israel.

1:44:56.202 --> 1:44:58.335
There's nothing I can do.

1:44:58.379 --> 1:44:59.554
I'm sorry.

1:44:59.597 --> 1:45:02.513
After everything I did
for this country,

1:45:02.557 --> 1:45:06.212
after all I gave them
when they begged me for money,

1:45:06.256 --> 1:45:07.301
for weapons.

1:45:07.344 --> 1:45:08.693
Doesn't she remember?

1:45:08.737 --> 1:45:12.088
This is how they repay me,
making me the only Jew

1:45:12.131 --> 1:45:15.221
in history to be banned
from his country.

1:45:15.265 --> 1:45:16.440
How dare she?

1:45:16.484 --> 1:45:18.224
How dare she?

1:45:19.965 --> 1:45:22.707
They've already arranged
for your return to the U.S.

1:45:22.751 --> 1:45:24.230
They're charging you
with contempt of court--

1:45:24.274 --> 1:45:25.362
Oh my God.

1:45:25.406 --> 1:45:27.103
And conspiracy related
to your ownership

1:45:27.146 --> 1:45:28.757
at the Flamingo Hotel.

1:45:28.800 --> 1:45:30.367
I won't go back there.

1:45:30.411 --> 1:45:33.152
I want you to help me
find a place,

1:45:33.196 --> 1:45:35.285
a country that will take me.

1:45:35.329 --> 1:45:36.242
I have money.

1:45:36.286 --> 1:45:38.157
Name the price.

1:45:38.201 --> 1:45:40.116
I don't want your money, Meyer.

1:45:40.159 --> 1:45:42.118
I believe your people
have betrayed you.

1:45:45.121 --> 1:45:46.514
I'll say.

1:45:52.694 --> 1:45:54.304
[Sighing]

1:45:54.348 --> 1:45:57.046
And after all that, they were
never able to indict you.

1:45:57.089 --> 1:45:58.308
[Sighs]

1:45:58.352 --> 1:46:01.572
The charges against me,
contempt of court,

1:46:01.616 --> 1:46:04.619
conspiracy, they were dropped.

1:46:08.013 --> 1:46:11.060
You can go back to Israel.

1:46:11.103 --> 1:46:13.323
[Laughs]

1:46:13.367 --> 1:46:17.240
The wandering Jew,
just like Lucky said.

1:46:21.679 --> 1:46:24.465
[Sighs]

1:46:24.508 --> 1:46:27.206
Have we arrived at the end
of my story?

1:46:33.212 --> 1:46:34.779
[Sighs]

1:46:39.088 --> 1:46:40.655
What about the money?

1:46:49.359 --> 1:46:50.447
Hmm.

1:46:52.014 --> 1:46:54.451
Come for a ride.

1:47:36.101 --> 1:47:37.886
Buddy.

1:47:37.929 --> 1:47:47.809
[♪♪♪]

1:48:29.024 --> 1:48:30.678
Gangster?

1:48:34.682 --> 1:48:39.817
I'm an angel
with a dirty face.

1:48:49.610 --> 1:48:53.004
I think we're finished, David.

1:48:53.048 --> 1:48:54.571
Go home.

1:48:57.618 --> 1:48:59.445
To your family.

1:49:01.404 --> 1:49:03.537
Remember me.

1:49:03.580 --> 1:49:13.459
[♪♪♪]

1:49:22.077 --> 1:49:25.036
[Sobbing]

1:49:25.080 --> 1:49:35.003
[♪♪♪]

1:49:51.019 --> 1:49:56.285
DAVID: [Voice-over]
When all is said and done,
how do we measure ourselves?

1:49:58.679 --> 1:50:00.985
If Lansky taught me anything,
it's that

1:50:01.029 --> 1:50:02.552
there's only one measure
in this world

1:50:02.596 --> 1:50:04.032
that truly matters.

1:50:06.295 --> 1:50:07.688
We measure ourselves
through the eyes

1:50:07.731 --> 1:50:09.733
of the ones we love.

1:50:13.911 --> 1:50:15.739
[Taking deep breaths]

1:50:21.440 --> 1:50:22.659
DAVID: [Voice-over]
Somewhere on the stretch
of highway

1:50:22.703 --> 1:50:25.444
between Miami and home,
it all made sense.

1:50:25.488 --> 1:50:28.578
Lansky spent his life
trying to control the game,

1:50:28.622 --> 1:50:31.189
but in the end,
he knew there was one game

1:50:31.233 --> 1:50:35.063
that no one gets to control,
life itself.

1:50:35.106 --> 1:50:37.456
And you can try
to beat the odds.

1:50:37.500 --> 1:50:40.416
But the house always wins.

1:50:40.459 --> 1:50:41.765
Maybe all you need
every now and then

1:50:41.809 --> 1:50:43.593
is a winning streak.

1:50:50.556 --> 1:50:52.080
You wanted to see me?

1:50:52.123 --> 1:50:53.559
Yeah, come on in, Frank.

1:51:00.044 --> 1:51:02.264
We're shutting
the investigation down.

1:51:02.307 --> 1:51:04.092
Wait, what?

1:51:04.135 --> 1:51:05.093
Why?

1:51:05.136 --> 1:51:06.572
It's over, Frank.

1:51:10.489 --> 1:51:11.534
Who's killing it?

1:51:11.577 --> 1:51:13.318
The CIA?

1:51:21.022 --> 1:51:23.894
Before your time, sonny boy.

1:51:23.938 --> 1:51:33.817
[♪♪♪]

1:52:03.978 --> 1:52:13.857
[♪♪♪]

1:52:44.018 --> 1:52:53.897
[♪♪♪]

1:53:24.058 --> 1:53:33.937
[♪♪♪]

1:54:04.098 --> 1:54:13.977
[♪♪♪]

1:54:44.138 --> 1:54:54.017
[♪♪♪]

1:55:24.178 --> 1:55:34.057
[♪♪♪]

1:56:14.228 --> 1:56:24.107
[♪♪♪]

1:56:54.268 --> 1:57:04.147
[♪♪♪]

1:57:34.308 --> 1:57:44.187
[♪♪♪]

